column2: As you push through the last of the dense undergrowth, you stumble into a clearing by a river. The starlight here is just enough to reveal your surroundings. As you take in your new environment, you suddenly notice that the will-o'-the-wisp that led you here has vanished without a trace. \n\nYour breath is visible in the cold night air: you should act quickly if you want to survive the night. Starting a fire is now your only chance for salvation.

column2: Hello everyone! Card Survival: Fantasy Forest is finally here. We want to give a very big thanks to all our returning players from Tropical Island, and to all the new ones that are willing to give Fantasy Forest a try! As you know, this is an Early Access title, and is going to be so for some time. Probably 2 years or more. This game is much bigger and complex than Tropical Island so it's going to take more time. As was the case with our previous game, we hope you will enjoy the process and help us shape its content and experiences! Any feedback you have on things you like or not like is welcome, as well as any suggestions for the content you'd like to see next!
column3: Hello everyone! Card Survival: Fantasy Forest is finally here. We want to give a very big thanks to all our returning players from Tropical Island, and to all the new ones that are willing to give Fantasy Forest a try! As you know, this is an Early Access title, and is going to be so for some time. Probably 2 years or more. This game is much bigger and complex than Tropical Island so it's going to take more time. As was the case with our previous game, we hope you will enjoy the process and help us shape its content and experiences! Any feedback you have on things you like or not like is welcome, as well as any suggestions for the content you'd like to see next!

We hope Fantasy Forest can turn into a super deep and complete survival/life simulation. Let's make it the best possible survival experience together!

column2: With each step you take towards the glow, the will-o'-the-wisp moves just a bit further into the shadows. The underbrush claws at your bare skin, cold seeps into your bones, and the ground punishes your bare feet. \n\nYou take a moment to catch your breath. Despite your efforts, the light remains out of reach, yet its faint glow still calls you onward.
column3: 光に向かって一歩一歩進むたびに、ウィスプは少しずつ影の中に入っていく。下草があなたの素肌を引っ掻き、寒さがあなたの骨に染み込み、地面があなたの素足を罰する。\n\n息を整える。しかし、そのかすかな光は、まだあなたを先へ先へと誘う。

column2: You open your eyes to chilling darkness, the ground beneath you damp and unfamiliar. Naked and shivering, confusion clouds your mind. You try to focus as fear prickles at your senses: the sounds and textures around you suggest you are in a forest.\n\nSuddenly, you notice a solitary light, faintly glowing in the black void ahead.
column3: 目を開けると凍てつくような暗闇が広がり、地面が湿っていて見慣れない。裸で震えていると、頭が混乱してくる。恐怖が意識をチクチクと刺激する中、あなたは集中しようとする。 周囲の音や感触から、森の中にいることがわかる。\n\n突然、前方の暗闇の中でかすかに光る1つの光に気づく。
